title: Tunisia: Tunisair Takes Delivery On August 24 of Second A330
text:
Tunis — Tunisair will take delivery on August 24 of its new Airbus A330-200 thus bringing the number of its fleet to 30 aircraft, the national carrier announced in a recent press release. 
The new aircraft, called "Sidi Bousaid," will be ferried from Toulouse Blagnac Airport to Tunis Carthage Airport. Tunisia
